quickjs-oxide is an independent Rust implementation targeting observable
compatibility with QuickJS 2026-06-04. The QuickJS C implementation is neither
compiled nor linked into product builds.

The compatibility reference, algorithmic source map, and generated Unicode
identifier table data derive from the QuickJS release. Its complete MIT notice
is retained in LICENSES/QuickJS-MIT.txt.

The identifier properties ultimately derive from Unicode 17.0.0 UCD data,
including DerivedCoreProperties.txt. The complete Unicode License v3 copyright
and permission notice is retained in LICENSES/Unicode-3.0.txt.

See compat/upstream.toml for the pinned release archive and checksum. Rust
dependency licenses remain those published by their respective packages.

The generated Rust Unicode identifier tables retain the Unicode 17.0.0 data
from QuickJS 2026-06-04 libunicode-table.h. The source table checksum and
regeneration command are recorded beside the generated data.
